  <brief_title>An Observational Study of Xeloda (Capecitabine) Monotherapy in Patients With Colorectal Cancer (AXEL)</brief_title>
  <official_title>The Efficacy of Adjuvant Chemotherapy With Capecitabine (Xeloda) Monotherapy in Patients With Colon Cancer Stage III (Duke C) Considering the Histopathology of the Tumour (AXEL)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hoffmann-La Roche</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hoffmann-La Roche</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This observational study will evaluate Xeloda (capecitabine) monotherapy on the effect of
      disease-free survival in patients with colon cancer stage III (Duke C) after surgical
      resection. Data will be collected for 3 years.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
